08/02/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The government adopted a new action plan for EU accession Thursday (February 7th) that aims to accelerate the adoption of legislation required for EU membership. A total of 119 pieces of legislation would be adopted by the end of the year to speed up the course of accession talks, slowed recently by a controversial fishing zone Zagreb imposed. 
Also on Thursday, Croatian television station HRT said the government has almost finalised preparations to establish a new state agency for fighting high-level corruption and organised crime. According to the HRT, the establishment of a "Croatian FBI" awaits an official government decision. (Vjesnik, Vecernji List - 08/02/08; HRT, HINA - 07/02/08)
